OREGON ex rel. SMITH v. GLADDEN, WARDEN. No. 23,

Misc.

Decided October 9, 1961. Appellant pro se. Robert Y. Thornton, Attorney General of Oregon, and Harold W. Adams, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee. Per Curiam.

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed. Treating the papers whereon the appeal was taken as a petition for writ of certiorari, certiorari is denied.
